7:
Clara! Swing wide and try to catch
them both!
14:
Good work. Let's rush the monsters
over there!
23: Now! You've got them on the ropes!
33:
Look, I ain't one to meddle, but why
do you let him boss you around like
that?
41:
Light. That furball's been parked on
your shoulder every fight, tellin' you
what to do. You don't have to listen
to him, y'know?
48:
Maybe, but a fighter like you doesn't
need it. Wouldn't you rather do your
own thing?
52:
My own thing, huh? To be honest... I
never really liked mercenary work.
56: And you're tellin' us that NOW?
59:
Well, it USED to be my dream. But
everyone back home was against it,
even though they never complained
about the boys learning to
fight—and I'm way stronger!
60:
I struck out on my own and found
work, but... I dunno, it just wasn't
what I expected. It was so routine
and boring.
62:
Oh, except for the times I worked
with the Fellowship of Floof! That
doctor sure was something...
65:
And? Why'd you keep at it if you
didn't like it?
68:
I think part of me kept hoping I'd
land a contract somewhere I could
really apply myself.
71:
I was tired of always being given
easy tasks, but now I can put my
skills to use and give it all I've got!
72:
All this time, I'd been longing for a
challenge—for someone to see my
true potential. I just never realized
how bad I needed it until now.
80:
Yup! So yeah... I'm more than happy
to be working with him!
84: Mmm... Can't say I don't understand.
85:
If you don't mind Light tagging along
on Kaleidoscope runs, I won't
interfere. Sorry I butted in.
94:
Uhh, I don't want to interrupt, but the
waitress has been staring us down
with menus for about ten minutes
now...
103:
Another monster! Light, what should
I do?
111: You know what to do, Clara.
118:
You can do this. You don't need me
telling you how to fight.
126:
It was not my intention to
eavesdrop, but I did overhear you
talking, yes.
129:
The monster approaches. Go, Clara.
Show us what you can do.
138:
You're a true warrior, perfectly able
to dispatch a monster such as this.
139:
You saved me in my time of need.
You are just, and you are
courageous!
140:
Know that I trust you as much as
you trust me. Now go!
145: Oh... Light, I... I'll do my best!
151:
All right, all right, quit windin' her up.
Relax, we've fought a million of these
things.
156:
The battlefield is no place to relax,
Nimbus.
160:
Yeesh. Clara, I'll back you up if things
get ugly, so ignore that old prude
and go have some fun!
166:
I'b... *sniffle* I'b nod worried aboud
the fighd, I just... I'm jusht so happy, I—
169:
Aaaah, come on Clara, focus! I- I'll
show that monster what I'm made
of!
